The turning point came in 1980.
Orange County officials wanted to build a five-lane road through the city instead of the two-lane highway, the Kennedy Highway, which played a major role in the life of the community.
The expanding Orlando has already entered the city's western border via Interstate 4.
The proposal came when Eatonville was still standing after a difficult historical period.
Forced integration has, among other things, ended the community's relatively idyllic isolation.
