Anglican Bishop Tom Wright welcomed the results of the study.
"Faith should be practiced and in many cases it changes our personality", Wright added.
After the great results, the question is, if Leonardo or a similarly calibrated painter showed a picture of a madonna to the faithful, what effect would that have on their pain control?
Would a quality vision of the Virgin Mary mean even better results?
